    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-16T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-16T01:00:00-05:00" n="1009"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1009">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9327/5–1649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-16T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 16, 1949—2 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 16—7:09 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1035. Shanghai radio reported May 11 Sino-Soviet Hami-Ata air agreement renewed
                    for 5 years, but Tihwa’s 115 to Department, repeated Embassy Canton 40, May 9
                        [<hi rend="italic">5</hi>]<note n="34" xml:id="d1009fn34">Not
                        printed.</note> indicates draft still not approved. Suggest appropriate
                    inquiry by Embassy Canton as to status this and economic cooperation pact with
                    Soviets.</p>
                <p>Conclusion either [or] both such pacts would seem good opportunity for public
                    discussion, and inquiry—through Department or other information channels—whether
                    CCP intends comment such pacts with USSR along lines criticism Nationalist
                    Government agreements with US and others. Does CCP evaluate these new pacts with
                    USSR as another concession by Kmt “running dogs of imperialism”? Simultaneous
                    widespread broadcast terms of pact, if available, perhaps comparing them with
                    terms Sino–US agreements related fields, also believed worth Department’s
                    consideration.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated OffEmb Canton 423, Tihwa 38.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
